text: Emily Tokić (born 4 February 1998) is an Australian model and beauty pageant titleholder who was crowned Miss International Australia 2018. She represented Australia at the Miss International 2018 pageant. == Personal life == Emily was born and raised in Canberra. She spent 13 years competing, undertaking exams and performing ballet. She has started a degree in Law and Commerce from the University of Canberra. She knows Croatian and English languages. She does some modelling. === Miss Universe Australia 2018 === Emily finished as the 4th Runner-up and she was awarded Miss Toybox at Miss Universe Australia 2018 represented New South Wales on 28 June 2018 at Sofitel in Melbourne. === Miss International Australia 2018 === Emily began her pageantry career representing Australian Capital Territory in the Miss International Australia 2018 competition, which she won. She succeeded outgoing Miss International Australia 2017 and Miss International 2017 3rd Runner-up, Amber Dew. === Miss International 2018 === As Miss International Australia, she had the right to represent Australia in Miss International 2018 pageant in Tokyo, Japan where she finished in the Top 15. ==References== ==External links== *Miss International Official Website *Miss International Australia Official Website * Category:Living people Category:1998 births Category:People from Canberra Category:Australian female models Category:Australian beauty pageant winners Category:Australian people of Croatian descent Category:Miss International 2018 delegates Category:University of Canberra alumni
